CSP uses the waf build system (http://code.google.com/p/waf/). In order to
compile CSP, you first need to configure the toolchain, what operating system
to compile for, the location of required libraries and whether to enable 
certain optional features.

To configure CSP to build with the AVR32 toolchain for FreeRTOS and output
the compiled libcsp.a file to the currect directory, issue:

./waf configure --toolchain=avr32- --os=freertos --libdir=.

When compiling for FreeRTOS, the path to the FreeRTOS header files must be
specified with --with-freertos=PATH.

A custom CSP config file can be included with --with-csp-config=CONFIG. See 
include/csp/csp_config.h for a list of available options. The custom config
need only specify the options that differ from the default values.

The CAN drivers can be enabled by appending the configure option --with-can=CHIP,
where CHIP is one of 'socketcan', 'at91sam7a1', 'at91sam7a3' or 'at90can128'. 
Run ./waf configure --help to list the available configure options.

To build and copy the library to the location specified with --libdir, use:

./waf build install
